</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0E1879525714FFEFFCA3F9B5BC4FF7AD" blockId="3.[787,1382,1422,1850]" lastBlockId="3.[168,1381,1855,3468]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFCA3F9B5BC64F9C7" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[789,1112,1541,1574]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatellum">Rhinopoma muscatellum</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFC68F99CBCB1F9AC" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[990,1165,1580,1613]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">R. hardwickii</taxonomicName>
until A. F. De-Blase and colleagues in 1973 convincingly demonstrated differences between them, supporting their status as distinct species. With regard to larger size of individuals from eastern 
<collectingCountry id="76B039C25714FFEFFC6AF942BC29F8F2" box="[988,1045,1778,1811]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Iran</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="76B039C25714FFEFFBD1F942BD2FF8F2" box="[1127,1299,1778,1811]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, they proposed separate subspecific status of seicanum. Molecular analyses revealed that divergence between 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFB81F88FBCE9F881" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[1079,1237,1855,1888]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatellum">muscatellum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFA95F88FB8C4F869" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hardwickii">hardwickii</taxonomicName>
was even deeper than expected: 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFD7FF8D7BB5AF869" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[713,870,1895,1928]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatellum">muscatellum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFC1AF8D7BC45F869" authorityName="Benda" authorityYear="2009" box="[940,1145,1895,1928]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hadramauticum">hadramauticum</taxonomicName>
form a common clade with 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFEFEF83EB9CEF84E" baseAuthorityName="Brunnich" baseAuthorityYear="1782" box="[328,498,1934,1967]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microphyllum">microphyllum</taxonomicName>
and quite distant from the clade of other forms of 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFB7FF83EBD61F84E" authorityName="E. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1818" box="[1225,1373,1934,1967]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhinopoma</taxonomicName>
. Large genetic distance between samples of 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFCB8F806BBE8F836" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[782,980,1974,2007]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatellum">R. muscatellum</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="76B039C25714FFEFFB9CF806BCBEF836" box="[1066,1154,1974,2007]" name="Oman" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Oman</collectingCountry>
and those from 
<collectingCountry id="76B039C25714FFEFFF1BF86DB8DAF81F" box="[173,230,2013,2046]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Iran</collectingCountry>
(4-9-5-4% based on cytochrome-b), together with data on phenotype homogeneity of all Iranian samples including topotypic seianum, suggest a split of 
<taxonomicName id="C9A702D15714FFEFFB28F7B5BD58F7C7" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1903" box="[1182,1380,2053,2086]" class="Mammalia" family="Rhinopomatidae" genus="Rhinopoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muscatellum">R. muscatellum</taxonomicName>
into two distinct clades. Correspondingly, two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
